perienced instructors  Improve English skills AND test skills  Increase their test scores in all areas       Test Prep Quote    I wanted to tell you that I’ve already been given the TOEFL scores and I’m very happy. The test assignments were exactly the same we’ve been practicing. The course at UIC and all your tips were really helpful. I don’t think I could have scored so well without it.    Irene Lulo | Argentina        TOEFL and IELTS Test Prep Courses   Don’t see what you’re looking for? We can create custom on-campus courses, online courses or private instruction to fit your needs. Contact us!      TOEFL Preparation Course         Course Info   For summer 2020, this course will meet online. Classes will be synchronous: students log onto UIC Blackboard to join class at the scheduled course time.  This 10-week course is designed to prepare students for the challenges of the TOEFL iBT. The TOEFL iBT evaluates the four core language skills: speaking, listening, reading, and writing. Every problem tests as many as three language skills at once. This course helps students gain experience and confidence with the TOEFL iBT, leading to better test results.  During this course, you will:   Practice and learn key test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT  Learn techniques to build vocabulary  Improve listening comprehension skills  Write and receive feedback on practice essays  Improve test performance under time limits  Take a complete practice test of the TOEFL iBT   Dates and Times  Fridays (10 weeks) 9 a.m. – 1 p.m.   Summer : May 29 – Aug. 7 (no class 7/3)  Fall: Sept. 11 – Nov. 13   Saturdays (10 weeks) 9:30 a.m. – 1:30 p.m.   Summer: May 30 – Aug. 8 (no class 7/4)  Fall: Sept. 12 – Nov. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $975 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for TOEFL iBT Preparation          IELTS Preparation Course         Course Info   For summer 2020, this course will meet online. Classes will be synchronous: students log onto UIC Blackboard to join class at the scheduled course time.  This 8-week course gives an overview of what students can expect on the IELTS, then focuses on effective techniques for completing the reading, writing, listening, and speaking sections of the IELTS Academic test format. Students analyze sample tests to learn the different types of IELTS questions and practice the best ways to answer them.  During this course, you will:   Learn practical approaches to taking the IELTS Academic format  Practice specific techniques for each section of the test  Improve vocabulary needed for success on the IELTS   Dates and Times  Fridays (8 weeks) 9 a.m. – 1 p.m.   Summer: June 5 – July 31 (no class 7/3)  Fall: Sept. 18 – Nov. 6   Saturdays (8 weeks) 9 a.m. – 1 p.m.   Summer: June 6 – Aug. 1 (no class 7/4)  Fall: Sept. 19 – Nov. 7   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $775 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for IELTS Preparation          Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening         Course Info   This 5-week course focuses on learning the test-taking strategies necessary for succeeding on the Reading and Listening sections of the TOEFL iBT.  Self-paced presentations teach you test strategies, and your instructor assigns detailed practice exercises and provides individualized weekly feedback and advice.  In this course, you are able to work at your own pace reviewing presentations, studying vocabulary, and completing practice exercises and tests.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for answering each of the question types on the Reading and Listening sections of the test  Study vocabulary necessary for the TOEFL iBT test  Complete practice exercises and take numerous practice tests  Receive individualized instructor advice and guidance  Receive individualized instructor advice and guidance   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify types of questions that you are struggling with and apply strategies to answer these questions correctly  Improve your academic vocabulary  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $350  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Required Textbooks  You must purchase the textbook for this course on your own before the course starts. You have two options:  You can purchase these two separate textbooks (one for each skill):   Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL test: iBT Reading (text with CD-ROM)  Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL Test: iBT Listening (text with Audio CDs CD-ROM)   Or, you can purchase the following single textbook (all skills):  Longman Preparation Course for the TOEFL test: iBT (text with CD-ROM)    Register for Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening          Online TOEFL Prep: Writing         Course Info   This 5-week course combines grammar and writing instruction to help you prepare for the Writing section of the TOEFL iBT test. Course documents provide a review of problematic grammar concepts in order to help you produce error-free sentences, while self-paced presentations teach you about the appropriate content and organization of each of the two TOEFL Writing tasks. Every week, you will be asked to write one essay, and you will receive individualized feedback and advice from the instructor.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for responding to each of the two writing tasks  Study writing templates and useful phrases  Complete practice tasks and take a final writing practice test  Receive individualized instructor feedback and advice   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Improve the organization, content, and accuracy of your essays  Identify weaknesses in your writing and correct your own errors  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $400  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for Online TOEFL Prep: Writing          Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking         Course Info   This 4-week course focuses on learning the test-taking strategies necessary to succeed on the Speaking section of the TOEFL iBT.  Self-paced presentations teach you test strategies for each of the six TOEFL Speaking tasks, while speech templates help you organize and deliver an appropriate response. In this course, you work at your own pace reviewing presentations and sample speaking tasks and responses, and every week, you submit two recorded TOEFL Speaking responses to the instructor for individualized feedback and advice.  During this course, you will:   Build test-taking strategies for the TOEFL iBT test  Learn specific techniques for responding to each of the six speaking tasks  Study speaking templates and listen to sample responses  Complete practice tasks and take a final speaking practice test  Receive individualized instructor feedback and advice   By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify the speaking task types and know what is required to complete each task  Improve the organization, content, and clarity of your responses  Be a more effective and efficient test-taker   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 7  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – March 28  Summer Term A: May 29 – June 26  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 7   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $350  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking          Online TOEFL Prep – Complete Course Package         Course Info   If you need to improve your score in all 4 TOEFL sections, enroll in our complete course package (Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening, Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking, and Online TOEFL Prep: Writing) for a reduced tuition fee of $1,000 (a $100 discount). You can take these courses together in one semester or separately over three consecutive semesters.  Course Fee  $1,000  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.    Register for the Complete Course Package               Register for your Test Prep Course           Request More Information   Contact us to learn more about our TOEFL and IELTS Test Prep courses.    Request Info            Other Programs    Back to main content           English for International Professionals    Test Prep Courses    Online Courses    Chicago, Communication and Culture    Customized Programs    Tutoring & Editing    Testing Services                  UIC Logo        The Tutorium         Main Menu    Intensive English    Other Programs    Student Life    About Us    How to Apply      IEP    IEP Courses    IEP Tuition & Fees    IEP Start Dates    Pay Fees    Current Students      More Info    I-20 & Visa    English for International Professionals    Contact Us        Quick Links    Request Information    Apply    Pay Fees         Contact   Tutorium i